This paper is about natural language inference and neural models, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the limitations of these models in capturing logical inferences, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset and evaluates the performance of state-of-the-art models, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
